<title>DENMARK: Carlsberg drafting statement on UK ruling.</title>
<headline>Carlsberg drafting statement on UK ruling.</headline>
<dateline>COPENHAGEN 1997-06-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Danish brewer Carlsberg said Friday that it was drafting a statement on British government demands that Bass drop plans to take over the Danes' half of Carlsberg-Tetley and sell its existing 50 percent.</p>
<p>&quot;We are working on a press release. I cannot say when it will be ready,&quot; a spokeswoman told Reuters.</p>
<p>Carlsberg shares were suspended at 365.00 crowns shortly before the British announcment.</p>
<p>A dealer estimated that they would fall by 10 to 15 crowns when they resumed trading.</p>
<p>&quot;But it's hard to say, when we don't know the detaiils and have not yet heard from Carlsberg,&quot; he added.</p>
<p>--Steve Weizman, Copenhagen newsroom +45 33969650</p>
